race.comment: GALLANT SON (3) resumed with a tough win at Flemington over 1000m, under pressure a long way out with a big weight but proving too strong late. His form around some top 3yo's last time in reads very well and he should only improve going to 1100m here. Expect he tracks the pace and with any luck proves too good again. GRACIE'S RAIN (5) faded late in the Black Pearl at Geelong last time. The win here prior in BM78 company was very good when rolling along in front. She'll charge across and can give a bold sight. RUE DE ROYALE (4) is going well, a deserved winner two back and close up again last time. He should be right there again. SWEETHEARTED (6) was okay down the Flemington straight last time in a race dominated up on speed. The tempo looks strong here, he'll be flashing late. CELSIUS STAR (2) gave a good sight last time and has claims.
